&lt;p&gt;Glance is building the next frontier of commerce. We are pioneering AI-powered, discovery-led shopping experiences that move beyond traditional search toward inspiration, personalization, and real-time engagement. Our platform brings agentic commerce to life - where consumers don&#39;t just search, they discover. Through immersive experiences across mobile, lock screen, and connected TV, Glance enables brands and retailers to reach consumers earlier in their journey and drive measurable business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What should you know about joining Glance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Glance, we walk the talk — free yourself, dream big, and chase your passion. On joining, you&#39;ll have opportunities to make an immediate impact on mission-critical projects, as you work with highly capable and ambitious peer groups. Be rewarded for your autonomy even as you collaborate. Ideate, innovate, and inspire by leveraging bleeding-edge tech to disrupt consumer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a passionate, self-motivated, and detail-oriented leader who is committed to the success of our partners and consumers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Role summary&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Distribution Partnerships and Business Development owns Glance AI Japan&#39;s distribution strategy and the senior partner relationships that deliver it. The focus of this role is on the non-Telco / non-OEM vectors — retail and franchise channels (T-Gaia, electronics chains, convenience stores, mass retail), super-app and widget partners (LINE, Yahoo! JAPAN, SmartNews, PayPay, WidgetClub), and Smart TV-OS platforms (Google TV / Android TV, Fire TV, TCL, Hisense, LG). These are the surfaces where Japan-specific consumer behavior, faster deal cycles, and higher near-term reach combine to create Glance&#39;s most leveraged distribution moves.&lt;/p&gt;
